    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-12-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-12-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="245"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d245">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Bigelow</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 326.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-12-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 9, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have received your interesting despatch of the
                    20th ultimo, No. 198, informing me of your proceeding upon learning of the
                    arrival of Admiral Pareja and his fleet at Valparaiso, and the correspondence
                    which had passed between him and the Chilian government. In reply I have to
                    thank you for the suggestions therein contained, and to inform you that the
                    exercise of your influence in the interest of peace is approved. For more
                    explicit instructions upon the subject, and for your information as to the
                    attitude of the United States in this question, I have to invite your attention
                    to my despatch<note n="*" xml:id="d245fn1">See instruction to Mr. Adams, No.
                        1618.</note> No. 324, of the 8th instant, and its accompaniments.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Bigelow,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
